Does anybody take creatine?

I read about it as, aside from helping with excercise performance, increases cognitive energy and you don't get tolerant to it — so almost sorta a little bit kinda being an alternative to caffeine that you don't gain tolerance to

I used to take it, it really is pretty harmless and has helped a lot of people. I'm probably going to start taking it again when I start gaining weight again (even though it could still help when losing weight)'

I wouldn't say it's exactly an alternative to caffeine. I think I saw on one of Jeff Nippard's videos that caffeine could be viewed as one of the big 3 supplements (Protein Powder, creatine, and caffeine) although don't exactly know his specific reasonings.
